listing_desc:
The Warner River Produce Farmers Market CSA does NOT provide a standard boxed share each week. Instead, you choose from the products we offer, the quantities you need, when you want them. Pickup at 6 local farmers markets, at our farm stand, order online or home delivery. 

Renew anytime, No penalties, No expiration. Receive a 10% bonus when you purchase or at each renewal.
We grow and produce a diverse range of products year-round using sustainable/organic practices without any synthetic chemicals, pesticides or GMOs. We are not certified organic but we adhere to, or exceed, the standards.

listing_desc:
Fifer\'s Farm Store and Kitchen is a 4th generation family farm that is located in Camden-Wyoming and offers U-pick, seasonal events, ice cream, lunch options, baked goods, fresh fruits, veggies and unique local foods.

We participate in Farmers’ Markets in Lewes (Saturdays) and Rehoboth Beach (Tuesdays). Our U-Pick crops feature: strawberries, blueberries, sunflowers, zinnias, peaches, apples and pumpkins (all when in-season only).

We also offer an 18-week CSA Farm Box Program (Community Supported Agriculture). This is a subscription based program that features many member benefits and new home delivery in addition to three Pickup locations.

listing_desc:
At Raccoon Forks Farms, we raise fresh, healthy, chemical-free local food by farming sustainably and humanely and working to improve our soil health and fertility.  We also provide employment, one-on-one job coaching, and a great work environment to people who have disabilities and other barriers to employment.  All employees at the Farms receive the support they need to build skills and be successful on the job.  Together, we raise delicious eggs, produce, and chicken!

We are a licensed Iowa Egg Handler.
season_desc: We offer CSA shares of vegetables, eggs, and chicken.  We also offer "add-on" shares of fruit, bread, and mushrooms from other great local providers.  Most shares are available in full and half sizes.  The number of weeks per share depends on the share type.  Contact us or see our web site for details.

listing_desc:
Beet Generation Farm exists to nourish the wellbeing of the farmer, the land, and the community.  We grow responsibly cultivated and seriously delicious food, so that we may inspire and feed others from an authentic, kind-hearted core.  From this place we believe true kinship with the earth and one another are possible.  

At Beet Generation Farm we strive to provide nourishing and delicious food for our communities through a vibrant community supported agriculture (CSA) program and a buzzing farmer's market booth at the Santa Rosa Farmer's Market at the Luther Burbank Center (Sat 8:30 - 1:00 pm).  We put a lot of love into our veggies - singing to them almost every day.  We are excited to nourish the hearts, minds, and souls of you and your family.

listing_desc: For Oak Cliff’s farmers market is a strategy to mitigate the food desert in our community and to increase food sovereignty. Our USDA-funded farmers market supports local farmers, growers, and ranchers by providing development, training, and paying the overhead costs for farmers to take part in the markets. All products sold are 100% locally grown or made (within 150 miles). Free programs, nutrition demos, and health screenings available from our partners. SNAP EBT is accepted and FMPP WIC vouchers available. SNAP can be matched up to $30 with Double Up Food Bucks for free produce.

listing_desc: Blue Marble Farm is a small produce farm located in the hills of Genesee, PA. Owners Jeff and Lisa started the farm in 2005 with the premise that they could do more for their health, the health of the earth and the health of their community. With the advent of Big Agriculture and the growing dependence on processed food, many Americans have lost touch with the local farmer. Blue Marble Farm's vision is to use and protect the resources on their land and share the bounty of the harvest with their community through their CSA. Jeff and Lisa are passionate about tending the soil, educating consumers about the world of agriculture, and reviving a spirit of community through their farm.

listing_desc: Harvestly is an online Farmer's Market that delivers all local foods to your door. With no subscriptions or minimums, you can fully customize your Harvestly order and choose from farm-fresh produce, pasture-raised eggs, locally-caught seafood, grass-fed beef, baked goods, prepared meals, and more. Founded and run by Cal Poly students, Harvestly aims to build a more sustainable and healthy food system by connecting local farmers and food producers directly to consumers.

listing_desc:
Lynchburg Grows is a nonprofit urban farm. Our mission is to work with our community to provide access to healthy food and afford purposeful jobs to individuals with disabilities. We have a 200-member CSA program and an on-site Farm Store open every Thursday, 9am to 1pm, throughout the growing season. Whether customers shop at the Farm Store or join the CSA, they can get the produce we raise, using all organic methods, plus produce and fruit from other local farms, local eggs, and artisanal foods. A scholarship fund makes CSA memberships available to people who need financial help to join. SNAP/EBT users get 50% off their CSA memberships and Farm Store purchases of fruit and vegetables.

We also run a produce prescription program in partnership with Virginia Cooperative Extension, called FreshRx, which provides nutrition and cooking education along with free produce and we donate produce to area organizations working to help meet basic needs in the community.

We do not obtain produce nor products from stores. We have added Organic Nutritional Healing and Energy Technology Healing Products. This is the way to overall heath we are offer.

listing_desc:
Blooming Junction is an authentic 150-year-old farmstead.  We specialize in a broad selection of plants well suited to our local climate and conditions. You’ll find well-chosen selections of shade and fruit trees, berry plants, perennials, annuals, shrubs, ornamental grasses, groundcovers, herbs, and organic vegetable starts! 
We offer multiple CSA seasons throughout the year. Full & half shares available, as well as CSA Add-ons, like bread, berries & more! We grow over 200 different varieties of vegetables.
In our Farm Market, we offer many locally prepared and artisanal grocery items, as well as produce freshly harvested from our farm. We offer U-pick berries in the summer, a huge pumpkin selection in the fall, and fresh cut Christmas trees and wreath for the holidays.
season_desc: Our 2022 Fall Season starts the week of October 31st and ends the week of December 19th. Fall Bread Share available as a CSA Add-On. Enjoy a loaf of delicious, local, freshly-made bread in you weekly CSA box.

listing_desc:
Our goal with the Fresh Harvest program is to serve our members by providing an exceptional box full of fresh, good tasting locally grown fruits and vegetables year round. As much as possible, this includes organic produce, but in the winter months, much of the available organic produce comes out of Mexico. We focus on local first, organic when available. We believe that consumers should strive to eat more produce, period. Restricting oneself to organically grown produce limits the variety and nutrition available from eating locally and seasonally.

Thanks for your support of our farm, our employees, our community and our earth. We welcome you to our farm for a tour and we look forward to the opportunity to teach more consumers about farming, agriculture and the importance of eating a diet high in fruits and vegetables.

listing_desc:
Fable is a farm and food hub dedicated to sustainable agriculture and education. We believe that through dedication, hard work, and modern technological advancements in agriculture, we can provide the freshest produce all year round without the use of harmful pesticides.
From our farm to your table, Fable’s produce is sustainably grown in the Hudson Valley and truly set the standard of excellence in local fruit vegetable, and egg production.
location_desc:
Directions from Taconic North or Southbound:
– Take the Ossining Exit onto Route 134 West. Our farm will be 500 yards on your left. 


Directions from Croton / Ossining:
– Travel on Route 134 East. Our farm will be on your right just before you approach the Taconic. 


Directions from East (Route 100):
– Travel on Route 100 then turn right onto Route 134 West. Our farm is 500 yards after the Taconic on the left-hand side.
